<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Capsicum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Capsicum carassense" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carassense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Capsicum carassense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to south-eastern Minas Gerais State (Brazil), growing mainly in the Serra do 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Caraça">Caraca</normalizedToken>
and other nearby mountainous areas (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="F41" captionText="Figure 41. Distribution of C. carassense, C. ceratocalyx and C. chacoense" figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.200.71667.figure41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/695456" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">41</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
